content:
Anne, thanks for this as well! This is similar to what I had imagined:
Lean starts with evaluating f and spends all of its time doing this computations, hence the 100%
however, to compute f, very quickly it goes to evaluate g, hence the 2% jump.
the leftover computations are the two slow ones.
Ok, I think that this is compatible with what I had in mind! Thanks and sorry for the noise!
Damiano Testa has marked this topic as resolved.
